Package: transitiontrees
Type: Package
Title: Pathway Trees and Predictive Pathway Discovery in Sequence Data
Version: 0.1.2
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Mohammed",
           family = "Saqr",
           email = "saqr@saqr.me",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")))
Description: Discovers, ranks, and interprets predictive pathways in
    categorical sequence data. Fits a variable-depth pathway tree
    (prediction suffix tree; Ron, Singer and Tishby (1996)
    <doi:10.1023/A:1026490906255>) and exposes a pathway-centric
    application programming interface: most common pathways, most
    predictively divergent pathways, sharpest pathways, modal-flip
    diagnostics, and next-state predictions. Multiple pruning criteria
    (likelihood-ratio G-squared, Kullback-Leibler divergence, and the
    Akaike and Bayesian information criteria), smoothing for unseen
    contexts, and sequence sampling are supported. The fit and
    predictive surface are validated to machine precision against an
    independent external reference implementation of the model.
